{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Base directory for this skill: /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io/.claude-review/skills/paper-wiki\n\n# Paper Wiki Skill\n\nOperate the personal arxiv paper knowledge base at `/inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/cc-research/my-paper-wiki`.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- User mentions \"paper-wiki\", \"论文库\", \"我的论文\", \"wiki\"\n- User provides arxiv URLs/IDs to add\n- User asks about papers they've collected (topics, tags, citations)\n- User wants to search their paper collection\n- User wants to ingest, compile, or manage papers\n\n## Quick Reference\n\nAll operations use Python SDK — no need to start HTTP server.\n\n```python\nfrom paper_wiki.config import load_config\nfrom paper_wiki.models import load_paper_meta, save_paper_meta, Paper, read_section_md\nfrom paper_wiki.data.ingestion import ingest\nfrom paper_wiki.data.paper_store import PaperStore\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nconfig = load_config()\nstore = PaperStore(Path(config.wiki.papers_dir))\n```\n\n## Operations\n\n### Ingest a paper (download from arxiv)\n\n```bash\ncd /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/cc-research/my-paper-wiki\nuv run python -c \"\nfrom paper_wiki.data.ingestion import ingest\nfrom paper_wiki.config import load_config\nfrom pathlib import Path\nconfig = load_config()\ningest('2606.12345', Path(config.wiki.papers_dir), config.arxiv)\n\"\n```\n\nFor batch ingest, pass multiple IDs in a loop. Some papers may not have HTML versions (404 is normal).\n\n### List / search papers\n\n```bash\n# List all\nuv run paper-wiki list\n\n# Search by concept\nuv run paper-wiki search --concept \"flow matching\"\n\n# Search by dataset\nuv run paper-wiki search --dataset \"LibriSpeech\"\n\n# Exact paper lookup\nuv run paper-wiki search --paper 2410.06885\n```\n\nOr via Python:\n```python\n# List with filters\npapers = store.list_papers(status=\"read\", tag=\"TTS\")\n\n# Get single paper\npaper = store.get_paper(\"2410.06885\")\n# paper.title, paper.authors, paper.abstract, paper.tags, paper.citations, paper.contributions\n```\n\n### Read paper content\n\n```python\npaper_dir = store.get_paper_dir(\"2410.06885\")\n\n# Metadata\npaper = load_paper_meta(paper_dir)\n\n# Sections (require compilation first)\ncontent = read_section_md(paper_dir, \"method\")\n\n# Personal notes\nnotes = (paper_dir / \"notes.md\").read_text()\n\n# Experiment results\nfrom paper_wiki.models import load_yaml\nresults = load_yaml(paper_dir / \"results\" / \"results.yaml\")\n\n# Bibliography\nbib = load_yaml(paper_dir / \"bib.yaml\")\n```\n\n### Update paper\n\n```python\n# Change reading status\nstore.update_status(\"2410.06885\", \"reading\")  # unread / reading / read\n\n# Add note\nstore.add_note(\"2410.06885\", \"Key insight: the flow matching objective is equivalent to...\")\n\n# Edit tags\npaper = store.get_paper(\"2410.06885\")\npaper.tags.append(\"TTS/蒸馏\")\nsave_paper_meta(store.get_paper_dir(\"2410.06885\"), paper)\n```\n\n### Create obsidian stub\n\nAfter ingesting, create an empty obsidian markdown file for browsing:\n```python\nimport yaml\ntitle = paper.title.replace(\"/\", \"-\").replace(\"\\\\\", \"-\")\nfilename = f'{title} ({paper.arxiv_id}).md'\nobsidian_dir = Path(\"/inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/cc-research/my-paper-wiki/obsidian\")\n(obsidian_dir / filename).touch()\n```\n\n### Compile paper (LLM-powered section decomposition)\n\nRequires API key in config.yaml. Generates structured sections, contributions, citations, tags.\n```bash\n# Start server first\nuv run uvicorn paper_wiki.dashboard.app:create_app --factory --port 8080\n\n# Then compile\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/compile/2410.06885\n```\n\nOr batch compile all pending:\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/compile-all\n```\n\n### Sync obsidian with wiki\n\nFind obsidian notes not in wiki and ingest them:\n```bash\ncd /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/cc-research/my-paper-wiki\n# Extract arxiv IDs from obsidian filenames\nls obsidian/*.md | grep -oP '\\(\\K[0-9]{4}\\.[0-9]+' | sort > /tmp/obs_ids.txt\n# Some notes have IDs inside the file content instead\ngrep -rPh '\\d{4}\\.\\d{4,5}' obsidian/*.md | grep -oP '\\d{4}\\.\\d{4,5}' | sort -u >> /tmp/obs_ids.txt\n# Current wiki IDs\nls papers/ | grep -P '^\\d{4}\\.\\d{4,5}$' | sort > /tmp/wiki_ids.txt\n# Missing\ncomm -23 <(sort -u /tmp/obs_ids.txt) /tmp/wiki_ids.txt\n```\n\n## Key Paths\n\n| Item | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Wiki root | `/inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/cc-research/my-paper-wiki` |\n| Papers data | `papers/{arxiv_id}/` |\n| Obsidian vault | `obsidian/` |\n| Config | `config.yaml` |\n| Metadata indexes | `metadata/indexes/` |\n\n## Paper Directory Structure\n\n```\npapers/{arxiv_id}/\n├── meta.yaml          # Structured metadata (always present)\n├── {arxiv_id}.md      # Obsidian-compatible main entry\n├── {arxiv_id}.pdf     # Downloaded PDF\n├── {arxiv_id}.html    # Downloaded HTML (may not exist)\n├── bib.yaml           # Extracted bibliography (after compile)\n├── notes.md           # Personal annotations\n├── status.yaml        # Status tracking\n├── source/            # TeX source files\n├── sections/          # Structured decomposition (after compile)\n│   ├── problem.md\n│   ├── method.md\n│   └── ...\n└── results/           # Experiment results (after compile)\n    └── results.yaml\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Ingest is safe to run on existing papers (no-op on existing dirs)\n- Compile requires LLM API key and is slow — don't compile unless user asks\n- Obsidian filenames: `Title (arxiv_id).md`\n- Tags follow hierarchical taxonomy: `TTS`, `TTS/架构-NAR-Flow`, `TTS/控制-NL描述`\n- Citation types: `compared_with`, `supported_by`, `eval_by`\n"}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "db0a2bcd-9a0f-4744-b7a0-e57185ed69ed", "uuid": "ee98b273-4d2d-4906-8d12-e514d4fc947a", "timestamp": "2026-07-06T07:53:11.215Z", "isSynthetic": true}
