isory signals from the intrinsic\n                                          since annotation typically requires domain expertise, careful\n                                                                                                                   structure of audio signals rather than from manual annotations.\n                                          quality control, and repeated verification. Manual labeling may\n                                                                                                                   In doing so, it encourages models to capture latent temporal,\n                                          also introduce annotation bias and privacy risks, particularly\n                                                                                                                   spectral, and contextual regularities from raw audio. Such\n                                          when recordings contain sensitive acoustic information. For\n                                                                                                                   supervision is typically instantiated through carefully designed\n                                          instance, medical audio analysis requires trained healthcare\n                                                                                                                   proxy or pretext tasks, which define the learning objectives\n                                          professionals to annotate heart sounds or respiratory sig-\n                                                                                                                   used to extract general-purpose acoustic representations from\n                                          nals [5], [6], while environmental sound analysis often relies\n                                                                                                                   unlabeled audio.\n                               